(1838,'Joey King','1999-07-30',125025,NULL,'{}','Joey Lynn King (born July 30, 1999) is an American teen actress widely known for her starring role as Ramona Quimby in Ramona and Beezus, the 2010 adaption of Beverly Cleary\'s book series with the same title with Disney star Selena Gomez. She also released a single for the movie called \"Ramona Blue\".\n\nKing was featured in Battle: Los Angeles, where she played a girl named Kirsten, who was battling for her life with the help of many courageous Marines. Also in 2011 she co-starred in Crazy, Stupid, Love. In 2012 King had a role in Christopher Nolan\'s third Batman film, The Dark Knight Rises as a young Talia al Ghul.\n\nFrom Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia','Los Angeles - California - USA','','/lGoCVFe0M2Gbt9Q61SVefwnxVPX.jpg'),
(1839,'Warren Brown','1978-05-11',211521,NULL,'{}','From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia\n\nWarren Brown (born 11 May 1978) is an English actor and former professional Thaiboxer, well known for his roles as Andy Holt in teen soap opera Hollyoaks and Lee Hibbs in the three-part BBC drama series Occupation written by Peter Bowker. Brown was born in Warrington, Cheshire, England.\n\nDescription above from the Wikipedia article Warren Brown (actor), licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.','Warrington, Cheshire, England','','/P8C71ZhmO4IXskztNlR9OSXkHI.jpg'),
