(2920,'Chloe Bridges','1991-12-27',98272,NULL,'[\"Chloe Suazo \"]','From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia.\n\nChloe Bridges (born on December 27, 1991 in Louisiana, height 5\' 3¾\" (1,62 m)) is an American actress. She is best known for her roles as Zoey in the sitcom Freddie (2005–2006) and as Dana Turner in the 2010 television film Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam. She was up for the role of Mitchie Torres in the first Camp Rock film, but it ultimately went to Demi Lovato. She also appeared in the 2009 films Legally Blondes and Forget Me Not. In March 2012, Bridges was cast as Donna LaDonna in The CW\'s Sex and the City prequel, The Carrie Diaries, which premiered January 2013.','Thibodaux - Louisiana - USA','','/7j9F8UbqAaosPLd7p2bk51Swa72.jpg'),
