(3639,'Claude King','1875-01-15',100346,'1941-09-18','[\"Claude Ewart King\"]','Claude King was born on January 15, 1875 in Northampton,  Northamptonshire, England as Claude Ewart King. He is known for his work  on Arrowsmith (1931), Mystery of the Wax Museum (1933) and Behind That Curtain (1929). He was married to Violet Luddington and Evelyn Hall. He died on September 18, 1941 in Los Angeles, California.\n\nDate of Birth  15 January  1875, Northampton, Northamptonshire, England\n\nDate of Death  18 September  1941, Los Angeles, California','','','/40tK4xE66zp6BYnq0Y6l6PQCYFM.jpg'),
