(4262,'Ioan Gruffudd','1973-10-06',65524,NULL,'{}','​From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia.  \n\nIoan Gruffudd (born 6 October 1973) is a Welsh actor. Trained at the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art, he started off in Welsh language productions, then came to international attention as Fifth Officer Harold Lowe in the film Titanic (1997), and as Lt. John Beales in Black Hawk Down (2001).\n\nHowever, he is probably best known for playing the role of Horatio Hornblower in Hornblower, the British made-for-TV films (1998–2003) based on C.S. Forester\'s novels. Gruffudd\'s recent notable film roles include Lancelot in King Arthur (2004), Mister Fantastic (Reed Richards) in Fantastic Four (2005) and the sequel Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer (2007), and British slavery abolitionist William Wilberforce in Amazing Grace (2006). He played Tony Blair in W. (2008).','Cardiff - Wales - UK','','/i55A4qrsbXaJYIZqrywZE0xwErt.jpg'),
