(4734,'Jennifer Garner','1972-04-17',9278,NULL,'{}','Jennifer Anne Affleck (née Garner; April 17, 1972), better known as Jennifer Garner, is an American actress. Garner gained recognition on television for her performance as CIA agent Sydney Bristow in the thriller drama series Alias, which aired on ABC for five seasons from 2001 to 2006. While working on Alias, she gained minor roles in hit movies such as Pearl Harbor (2001) and Catch Me if You Can (2002). Since then, Garner has appeared in supporting as well as lead roles on the big screen in projects including Daredevil (2003), 13 Going on 30 (2004), Elektra (2005), a spin-off of Daredevil and Juno (2007). She is married to actor and director Ben Affleck, with whom she has two daughters.\n\nDescription above from the Wikipedia article Jennifer Garner, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.','Houston - Texas - USA','','/8LYwRdKGImU1uUWBNhcL95ZqysK.jpg'),
